Text:
Video: DivX 3 640x352 23.98fps 971Kbps 
Audio: MPEG Audio Layer 3 48000Hz stereo 119Kbps 

Decent, watchable Dvd rip.  It could stand to be re-ripped and encoded in a modern codec, as there is minor, but noticeable artificating in a few scenes.

The best encode I can reasonably expect from this era.
